[
    {
        "source_sentence": "南天竺國菩提達摩禪師觀門",
        "translation": "Meditation Gate of the Bodhidharma Master of Southern India",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b03_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "問曰。",
        "translation": "The question was, \"What is meditation?",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b05_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "何名禪定　答曰。",
        "translation": "\"What's called meditation?\" The answer is.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b05_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "禪為亂心不起無動無念為禪定。",
        "translation": "\"Meditation is the absence of disturbances in the mind, and the absence of movement and mindfulness is considered meditative concentration.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b05_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "端心止念。",
        "translation": "He correctly calms his mind and stops mindfulness.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b06_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無生無滅。",
        "translation": "There's no arising or ceasing, and there's no going or coming.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b06_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無去無來。",
        "translation": "There's no going and no coming.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b06_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "堪然不動。",
        "translation": "It's called meditation that's calm and unmoving.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b07_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "名之為禪定　何名為禪觀　答曰。",
        "translation": "This is called meditation. What's called meditative contemplation? Answer: 'The mind's mental clarity is called meditation.'",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b07_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "心神澄淨名之為禪。",
        "translation": "The mental clarity of the mind is called meditation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b08_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "照理分明名之為觀。",
        "translation": "When the principle is clearly illuminated, it's called contemplation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b08_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "禪觀自達無有錯謬。",
        "translation": "Self-acquisition of meditation and contemplation has no errors.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b09_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名禪觀。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called meditation and contemplation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b09_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "心神澄淨不生不滅不來不去湛然不動名之為禪　問曰。",
        "translation": "When the mind's spirit is purified, it doesn't arise or cease, doesn't come or go, and remains motionless, that's called meditation. Q. What's the name of meditation?",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b09_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "何名禪定　答曰。",
        "translation": "\"What's the name of meditation?\" The answer is.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b11_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "禪定者梵音。",
        "translation": "\"Meditation\" is the Sanskrit sound.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b11_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此名功德聚林。",
        "translation": "It's called the forest of merit.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b11_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "三界諸佛皆說禪坐。",
        "translation": "The buddhas of the three realms all say to sit in meditation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b12_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名功德聚林　又問。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the forest of merits. Again, he asked.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b12_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "何名禪法　答曰。",
        "translation": "\"What's called the method of meditation?\" The answer was.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b13_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "禪法從通有次第。",
        "translation": "\"The dharma of meditation has a sequence from its penetration.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b13_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "初學時從始終有七種觀門。",
        "translation": "When you first train, there are seven ways to contemplate from beginning to end.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b13_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第一住心門。",
        "translation": "The first is the gate of abiding in mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b14_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第二空心門。",
        "translation": "The second is the gate of emptiness of mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b14_12",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第三無門。",
        "translation": "The third is the gate of nonexistence.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b15_13",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第四心解脫門。",
        "translation": "The fourth is the gate of the mind's liberation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b15_14",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第五禪定門。",
        "translation": "The fifth is the gate of meditation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b15_15",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第六真妙門。",
        "translation": "The sixth is the gate of true marvelousness ...",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b16_16",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第七智慧門。",
        "translation": "And the seventh is the gate of wisdom.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b16_17",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "住心門者。",
        "translation": "\"The gate of abiding in the mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b16_18",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂心散動攀緣不住。",
        "translation": "It means the mind is distracted, doesn't cling to objects, and doesn't abide.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b16_19",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "專攝念住更無去動。",
        "translation": "It's exclusively collected in mindfulness and abides without any further movement.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b17_20",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名住心門。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the gate of abiding in the mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b17_21",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "空心門者。",
        "translation": "\"Gate of emptiness\" means the mind is empty and tranquil.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b18_22",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂看心轉追覺心空寂。",
        "translation": "It means to look at the mind and pursue it, realizing that the mind is empty and quiescent.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b18_23",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無去無來無有住處。",
        "translation": "There's no going, no coming, and no abiding place.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b18_24",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無所依心。",
        "translation": "There's no mind that has anything to rely on.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b19_25",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故云空心門。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the gate of emptiness of mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b19_26",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "心無相門。",
        "translation": "The aspect of the mind having no characteristics.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b19_27",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂心澄淨無有相貌。",
        "translation": "It means the mind is pure and lacks characteristics.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b20_28",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "非青非黃非赤非白。",
        "translation": "It's not blue, not yellow, not red, and not white.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b20_29",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "非長非短非大非少。",
        "translation": "It's neither long nor short, neither large nor small.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b21_30",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "非方非圓湛然不動。",
        "translation": "It's neither square nor round, and it's perfectly motionless.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b21_31",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名無相門。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the approach of marklessness.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b22_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "心解脫門者。",
        "translation": "\"He who goes through the gate of mental liberation ...",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b22_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "知心無繫無縛。",
        "translation": "He knows that his mind is unfettered and unfettered.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b22_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "一切煩惱不來上心。",
        "translation": "All afflictions don't come up to the mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b22_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名心解脫門。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the gate of liberation of the mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b23_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "禪定者。",
        "translation": "\"Meditation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b23_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "西域梵音。",
        "translation": "It's a Sanskrit word from the West.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b23_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "唐言靜慮。",
        "translation": "The Tang term for it is meditation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b24_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "覺心寂靜。",
        "translation": "He awakens to the quiescence of his mind.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b24_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "行時住時坐時臥時皆悉寂靜無有散動。",
        "translation": "When walking, standing, sitting, sitting, and lying down, they're all still, and there's no agitation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b24_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名寂靜。",
        "translation": "That's why it's called quiescence.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b25_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "真如門者。",
        "translation": "He's a practitioner of the gate of true thusness.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b25_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "覺心無心等同虛空。",
        "translation": "He perceives mind and no mind as being the same as space.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b26_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "遍周法界平等不二。",
        "translation": "It completely pervades the Dharma realm with equality and nonduality.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b26_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無千無變。",
        "translation": "There are no thousands, and nothing changes.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b26_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名真如門。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the gate of true thusness.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b27_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "智慧門者。",
        "translation": "\"The gate of wisdom.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b27_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "識了一切名之為智。",
        "translation": "To comprehend everything is called wisdom.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b27_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "契達空源名之為慧。",
        "translation": "Understanding the source of emptiness is called wisdom.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b28_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名智慧門。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called the gate of wisdom.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b28_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "亦名究竟道。",
        "translation": "It's also called the ultimate path.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b28_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "亦名大乘無相禪觀門。",
        "translation": "It's also called the gate of great vehicle markless meditation and contemplation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b29_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "則是修禪學道故。",
        "translation": "It's because it's the path of cultivating meditation and training.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270b29_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "禪有七種觀門。",
        "translation": "There are seven kinds of contemplative approaches in meditation.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c01_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "大聲念佛得十種功德。",
        "translation": "Remembering the Buddha in a loud voice obtains ten kinds of merit.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c01_12",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "一者不聞惡聲。",
        "translation": "One, they won't hear bad sounds.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c02_13",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "二者念佛不散。",
        "translation": "Two, mindfulness of the Buddha doesn't scatter.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c02_14",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "三者排去睡眠。",
        "translation": "Three, he rids himself of drowsiness.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c02_15",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "四者勇猛精進。",
        "translation": "Four, he vigorously undertakes exertion.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c03_16",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "五者諸天歡喜。",
        "translation": "Five, the gods rejoice.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c03_17",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "六者魔軍怖畏。",
        "translation": "Six, the armies of Māra are terrified.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c03_18",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "七者聲振十方。",
        "translation": "Seven, his voice resounds in ten directions.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c04_19",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "八者三途息苦。",
        "translation": "Eight, the three paths are calmed by suffering.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c04_20",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "九者三昧現前。",
        "translation": "Nine, samādhi is manifested.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c04_21",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "十者往生淨土。",
        "translation": "Ten, he'll be reborn in the Pure Land.",
        "source": "T85n2832_001:1270c05_22",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    }
]